00:09:46,392 --> 00:09:50,594
in understanding marginalized communities and their voices.

219
00:09:50,594 --> 00:09:53,595
And by that, I mean groups that are often not included

220
00:09:53,595 --> 00:09:55,536
as part of the status quo.

221
00:09:55,536 --> 00:09:56,796
They've been othered in society,

222
00:09:56,796 --> 00:09:58,377
either implicitly or explicitly,

223
00:09:58,377 --> 00:10:02,519
due to differences in race, gender, sexuality,

224
00:10:02,519 --> 00:10:06,000
disability, socioeconomic status, and religion, and so forth.

225
00:10:07,852 --> 00:10:09,994
And I wanted to be part of including and appreciating

226
00:10:09,994 --> 00:10:13,777
different voices outside of non-profits.

227
00:10:13,777 --> 00:10:15,799
Like, non-profits, when you're already

228
00:10:15,799 --> 00:10:17,780
a community of activists, it's quite easy

