00:10:22,744 --> 00:10:28,769
What I wanted to do was actually work at an organization.

232
00:10:28,769 --> 00:10:31,391
Because really, I wanted to normalize D&I.

233
00:10:31,391 --> 00:10:33,673
I wanted to have it be something that we all can talk about

234
00:10:33,673 --> 00:10:36,035
and that we all feel pretty comfortable talking about.

235
00:10:37,704 --> 00:10:41,285
At first it was mostly about boosting marginalized voices,

236
00:10:41,285 --> 00:10:43,966
but to also raise the quality bar

237
00:10:43,966 --> 00:10:45,347
of teams in creative spaces.

238
00:10:45,347 --> 00:10:49,368
So when Riot was looking for a manager of D&I programs,

239
00:10:49,368 --> 00:10:51,149
I thought, this is the kind of role

240
00:10:51,149 --> 00:10:52,750
I've been working towards.

241
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:56,111
You know, like despite the twists and turns in my life,

242
00:10:56,111 --> 00:10:58,452
like a common thread is that I'm a pretty political person.

243
00:10:58,452 --> 00:11:00,893
It's really difficult for me to view the world

244
00:11:00,893 --> 00:11:04,254
in a way that's not influenced by my gender or my race.

245
00:11:04,254 --> 00:11:06,095
That's always kind of a prevalent lens.

246
00:11:07,860 --> 00:11:10,781
And this didn't change when I talked about games

247
00:11:10,781 --> 00:11:13,702
or worked within them or mentored folks.

248
00:11:13,702 --> 00:11:14,602
So in case this is a relatively new topic

249
00:11:14,602 --> 00:11:16,983
